    <div class="content grid_16 prefix_2">
      <h2>History</h2>
    
      <p>Brightbox has its roots back in 2005, hosting Ruby on Rails apps on dedicated hardware. In 2007 we switched to providing virtualized services using Xen technology.</p>

<p>Firmly focused on Rails deployment, we grew rapidly in popularity, hosting fully managed apps for large companies such as Amnesty International, Channel4, MTV and many more.</p>

<p>In 2010, we began work on a whole new platform built from the ground up. After almost 18 months of development, Brightbox Cloud was launched in September 2011.</p>
      
    </div><!-- /content -->
    
  </div><!-- /container_24 -->
</div><!-- /banner -->

