</div><section class='feature' id='cloud_servers'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>High performance and flexible Cloud Servers.</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>Billed by the minute, ready in seconds.</h4>

<div class='grid_13 alpha'>
<p>Brightbox Cloud Servers are on-demand, performance-optimised virtual machines, backed by enterprise-grade hardware and lightning-fast persistent storage. In addition, Brightbox Cloud uses KVM, which provides significant performance gains over Xen (as used by Amazon EC2 and Rackspace Cloud).</p>

<p>Our high performance and highly available network provides each of your Cloud Servers with its own separate network segment, secure from spoofing or eavesdropping.</p>
</div>

<div class='grid_9 prefix_2 omega'>
  
  <p><img src='/images/os_logos.png' alt='Use any OS' style='margin:25px 0 10px 0' /></p>
  
  <p>Use any OS, perhaps <a href='#image_library'>bring your own</a>, or even PXE boot "bare metal" and install direct from the Internet!</p>

  <p>Out-of-band access to your Cloud Servers is provided by an encrypted graphical console.</p>


  <p><strong><a href='/pricing/#cloud_servers'>Cloud Server pricing &rsaquo;</a></strong></p>

</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>

</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='zones'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Geographically isolated datacentre "Zones".</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>Effortlessly build highly-available systems which span multiple Brightbox datacentres.</h4>

<div class='grid_12'>
<p>Zones are physically separate Brightbox datacentre locations interconnected by our Brightbox Rapid Convergence Routing Fabric.</p>

<p>For geographic redundancy, simply create <a href='#cloud_servers'>Cloud Servers</a> in multiple Zones and use <a href='#load_balancers'>Load Balancing</a> to distribute traffic across them.</p>
</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='cloud_ips'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Instantly mappable Cloud IP addresses.</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>Move IPv4 addresses between your Cloud Servers and Load Balancers.</h4>

<div class='grid_13 alpha'>
<p>Cloud IPs are public IPv4 addresses that you can instantly map to a <a href='#cloud_servers'>Cloud Server</a> or <a href='#load_balancers'>Load Balancer</a>.</p>

<p>Grow and migrate your Brightbox Cloud applications seamlessly: Start with a single Cloud Server, then add a Load Balancer, then move back to a single server, then to a Server in a separate Zone - all without having to update DNS!</p>

<p><strong><a href='/pricing/#cloud_ips'>Cloud IP pricing &rsaquo;</a></strong></p>

</div>


<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='load_balancers'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Cloud Load Balancers.</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>Geographic redundancy, fault tolerance and horizontal scalability for your app, in seconds.</h4>

<div class='grid_17 alpha'>
<p>Add fault tolerance and horizontal scalability to your systems by balancing traffic across a pool of <a href='#cloud_servers'>Cloud Servers</a> in multiple <a href='#zones'>Zones</a>. Brightbox Load Balancers are highly available across a Region - designed to tolerate the loss of an entire Zone without disruption!</p>

<p>Each Load Balancer can balance multiple protocols at once (HTTP, SSH, FTP etc) and can comfortably handle 5000 concurrent connections, with additional scaling options available soon.</p>

<p><strong><a href='/pricing/#load_balancers'>Load Balancer pricing &rsaquo;</a></strong></p>

<p><a href='#screencast_loadbalancers' class='zoom screencast'>Watch screencast</a></p>
</div>


<div id='screencast_loadbalancers'>
<object height='495' classid='clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000' width='820' codebase='http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0'><param name='allowFullScreen' value='true' /><param name='allowscriptaccess' value='always' /><param name='src' value='http://www.youtube.com/v/03zdxQPEnPI&amp;version=3&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en_GB&amp;rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;theme=light&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;autohide=1' /><param name='allowfullscreen' value='true' /><embed src='http://www.youtube.com/v/03zdxQPEnPI&amp;version=3&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en_GB&amp;rel=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;theme=light&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;autohide=1' allowfullscreen='true' type='application/x-shockwave-flash' allowscriptaccess='always' height='495' width='820' /></object>
</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>

</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='image_library'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>No-fuss import/export of your Cloud Server images and snapshots.</h3>

<h4 class='subtitle'>Upload your own images and download your snapshots with ease. No lock-in here!</h4>

<div class='grid_7 prefix_16'>
<p>Managing <a href='#cloud_servers'>Cloud Server</a> images is a breeze with Brightbox - simply upload your OS images and download your snapshots as raw disk images via FTPS.</p>

<p>Share your OS images with other Brightbox users by making them "public".</p>


</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='api'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Powerful API tools.</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>RESTful interaction with Brightbox Cloud.</h4>

<div class='grid_9'>
<p>We provide a very easy-to-use <a href='http://docs.brightbox.com/guides/cli/getting-started.html'>command-line interface</a> (CLI) which interacts with our <a href='https://api.gb1.brightbox.com/1.0/'>RESTful API</a>.</p>

<p>There are also higher level <a href='http://docs.brightbox.com/references/api.html'>Ruby and Python libraries</a> available to get you started quickly.</p>

<p>Our flexible OAuth-based authentication system gives you fine grained control over who or what has access to your account and resources via the API.</p>
</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='metadata_service'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Instance metadata service compatible with Amazon EC2</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>Bring your AMIs to Brightbox!</h4>

<div class='grid_9 prefix_14'>
<p>Automatically install your SSH public keys and configure your Cloud Servers at launch-time.</p>
  
<p> Our <a href='http://docs.brightbox.com/references/metadata-service.html'>metadata service</a> is compatible with Amazon EC2, enabling easy reuse of your AMIs on Brightbox.</p>
</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
