</section><section class='feature' id='api'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Powerful API tools.</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>RESTful interaction with Brightbox Cloud.</h4>

<div class='grid_9'>
<p>We provide a very easy-to-use <a href='http://docs.brightbox.com/guides/cli/getting-started.html'>command-line interface</a> (CLI) which interacts with our <a href='https://api.gb1.brightbox.com/1.0/'>RESTful API</a>.</p>

<p>There are also higher level <a href='http://docs.brightbox.com/references/api.html'>Ruby and Python libraries</a> available to get you started quickly.</p>

<p>Our flexible OAuth-based authentication system gives you fine grained control over who or what has access to your account and resources via the API.</p>
</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
</section><section class='feature' id='metadata_service'>
<div class='inner'>
<a href='#top' class='back_to_top'>&uarr; Back to top</a>

<h3>Instance metadata service compatible with Amazon EC2</h3>
<h4 class='subtitle'>Bring your AMIs to Brightbox!</h4>

<div class='grid_9 prefix_14'>
<p>Automatically install your SSH public keys and configure your Cloud Servers at launch-time.</p>
  
<p> Our <a href='http://docs.brightbox.com/references/metadata-service.html'>metadata service</a> is compatible with Amazon EC2, enabling easy reuse of your AMIs on Brightbox.</p>
</div>

<div class='clear'>.</div>
</div>
</section>
