"3<%= render "blog_archive", @item.attributes %>;@u""/about/working-for-brightbox/{;{	;"f<p>We work to ensure our team have a comfortable, productive working environment, free from the bureaucracy and frustrations commonly associated with office life.</p>

<h3 id='working_from_home'>Working from home</h3>

<p>We mostly work from home ‚Äì we don‚Äôt need to sell the joys of working from home. It&#8217;s great.</p>

<p>We&#8217;ve got plenty of systems in place to make the most of teleworking - a private Jabber server for short, daily meetings and chat throughout the day; VOIP conference calls; <a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Redmine'>Redmine</a> for project management; and a private wiki for documentation.</p>

<h3 id='our_leeds_office'>Our Leeds office</h3>

<p>Our team is spread across two continents, but we have a base office in Leeds, United Kingdom. It&#8217;s just outside Leeds city centre and is easily accessible - there‚Äôs free parking and it&#8217;s on good public transport links from around the city.</p>

<p>Some of us meet up at the office once every couple of weeks, mostly just to catch up with each other and eat great <a href='http://www.dutchpotleedsltd.co.uk/'>Caribbean food</a>.</p>

<h3 id='scrumstyle_development'>SCRUM-style development</h3>

<p>We use SCRUM-style practices for our development project management - we&#8217;ve taken the bits that are most useful to us and left out the jargon and the filler.</p>

<p>We work in focused sprints, no more than a fortnight at a time, with planning and review meetings at the start and end of the sprint, and daily catch-up meetings throughout the run.</p>

<h3 id='support_for_the_ror_and_free_software_communities'>Support for the RoR and Free Software communities</h3>

<p>We wouldn&#8217;t be where we are today without the work of the Ruby on Rails and other <a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_software'>free software</a> communities so we do what we can to support them.</p>

<p>We commit time and resources to make and <a href='https://github.com/brightbox'>release useful tools and scripts</a>. We release libraries and full applications. We support grassroots events both financially and logistically as well as attending them.</p>;	"#<!DOCTYPE html>
