<h3>Read.</h3>

<p><strong><a href='/blog'>Our blog</a></strong> is a great place to read about what&#8217;s going on at Brightbox (we also have a <a href='http://blog.brightbox.co.uk'>Ruby-focused blog</a> which covers our Ruby platform).</p>

<h3>Learn.</h3>

<p><strong><a href='http://docs.brightbox.com'>Our documentation</a></strong> is a great place to get started and is freely available <a href='https://github.com/brightbox/brightbox-docs'>on Github</a> under a creative commons license, contributions are welcome!</p>

<h3>Help.</h3>

<p><strong><a href='http://forum.brightbox.com'>The forums</a></strong> are a great place to get (and give) help, or just chat with other Brightbox users.</p>

<h3>Chat.</h3>

<p>We have an irc channel on <a href='http://freenode.net/'>Freenode</a> for real-time chat, join <strong><code>#brightbox</code></strong> on <code>chat.freenode.net</code>.</p>
</div><div class='grid_11 prefix_2'>
<h3>Fork.</h3>

<p>We&#8217;ve built and released quite a bit of code, from full apps and libraries to contributions to other projects. You can find it all on <a href='https://github.com/brightbox'>our Github account</a>.</p>

<h3>Suggest.</h3>

<p>Got an idea for a feature? Want to help shape Brightbox Cloud? Get involved on the <a href='https://brightbox.uservoice.com'>feedback forum</a>.</p>

<h3>Meet.</h3>

<p>We sponsor, speak at and attend local grassroots events and meet-ups. If you&#8217;ve got an event you&#8217;d like us to speak at or sponsor, <a href='/contact'>get in touch</a></p>

<h3>Follow.</h3>

<p>We&#8217;re on Twitter, like all the cool kids: <a href='http://twitter.com/brightbox'>@brightbox</a></p>
