<div class="post">
  <h2><a href="/blog/2011/03/25/ipv6-brightbox-cloud/">IPv6 in the Brightbox Cloud</a></h2>

  <p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1887" title="ipv6 ping" src="http://blog.brightbox.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/bb-ping-cloud-ipv62.png" alt="" width="628" height="128" /></p>

<p>I don‚Äôt have to tell you why IPv6 is important ‚Äì even the mainstream media has finally realised that the pool of IPv4 addresses is exhausted (it‚Äôs not like we needed tarot cards to predict it!). Any modern network must have support for IPv6.</p>

<p>We‚Äôve been concentrating on perfecting IPv4 in <a href="http://beta.brightbox.com/beta">Brightbox Cloud</a> as that‚Äôs the immediate need, but we‚Äôve considered IPv6 since day one of our network designs (over a year ago now!).  Every cloud server will get IPv6 addresses by default (and AAAA dns records of course), so you‚Äôll be able to access your servers directly. We already have this working for our own test servers and we‚Äôll have it in the hands of our customers very soon.</p>

<p>IPv6 will be a ‚Äúfirst class citizen‚Äù in the Brightbox Cloud ‚Äì supported throughout all of our services: Our Cloud Servers, Load Balancers, Firewall, Cloud IPs and of course <a href="https://api.gb1.brightbox.com/1.0/">our API</a>. We‚Äôre currently working on the full implementation but I thought it was worthwhile announcing our plans, since this is such an important aspect of our service.</p>


  
  <p class="details">
    <span class="date">posted 25 Mar 2011
    
  
    by <a href="/author/john">John Leach</a>
  
    </span>
  </p>
</div><!-- /post -->

      
        <!-- Snippet for displaying a blog post content in paginated page -->
<div class="post">
  <h2><a href="/blog/2010/11/09/announcing-brightbox-cloud-the-uks-first-true-iaas-platform/">Announcing Brightbox Cloud ‚Äì the UK‚Äôs first true IaaS platform!</a></h2>

  <p>Today, we‚Äôre announcing the private beta launch of <a href="http://beta.brightbox.com">Brightbox Cloud</a> ‚Äì our new IaaS (Infrastructure-as-a-Service) platform!</p>

<p>We‚Äôve dedicated several months to developing and engineering our new cloud platform from the ground up (almost literally). We‚Äôve kitted out two new datacentre ‚ÄúZones‚Äù, set up a new resilient network across them and built-out a distributed cloud system which enables some very exciting features such as re-mappable cloud IP addresses, easy import/export of your cloud server images and much, much more.</p>

<p>We‚Äôre launching the private beta phase with our <a href="http://docs.brightbox.com/guides/getting_started">simple command-line client</a> (a full control panel GUI will be available soon). Check out the screencast below to see how easy it is to get started.</p>

<p>If you‚Äôd like to get [free] access to our private beta programme, simply <a href="http://beta.brightbox.com/beta#signup">submit a request via the beta site</a> and we‚Äôll be in touch shortly!</p>

<p>I‚Äôm extremely proud of our achievement, Brightbox is the first company in the UK to offer a ‚Äú<a href="http://beta.brightbox.com/beta#faq-true">true</a>‚Äù distributed IaaS cloud ‚Äì quite a shake-up for the European cloud market. Stay tuned ‚Äì there‚Äôs a lot more in store!</p>

<object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="630" height="410" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" />
<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />
<param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/XwkJx5QgclA?fs=1&amp;hl=en_GB&amp;rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" />
<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />
<embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="630" height="410" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/XwkJx5QgclA?fs=1&amp;hl=en_GB&amp;rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" /></object>

  
  <p class="details">
    <span class="date">posted 09 Nov 2010
    
  
    by <a href="/author/jeremy">Jeremy Jarvis</a>
  
    </span>
  </p>
</div><!-- /post -->

      

