  <h2><a href="/blog/2010/11/09/announcing-brightbox-cloud-the-uks-first-true-iaas-platform/">Announcing Brightbox Cloud ‚Äì the UK‚Äôs first true IaaS platform!</a></h2>

  <p>Today, we‚Äôre announcing the private beta launch of <a href="http://beta.brightbox.com">Brightbox Cloud</a> ‚Äì our new IaaS (Infrastructure-as-a-Service) platform!</p>

<p>We‚Äôve dedicated several months to developing and engineering our new cloud platform from the ground up (almost literally). We‚Äôve kitted out two new datacentre ‚ÄúZones‚Äù, set up a new resilient network across them and built-out a distributed cloud system which enables some very exciting features such as re-mappable cloud IP addresses, easy import/export of your cloud server images and much, much more.</p>

<p>We‚Äôre launching the private beta phase with our <a href="http://docs.brightbox.com/guides/getting_started">simple command-line client</a> (a full control panel GUI will be available soon). Check out the screencast below to see how easy it is to get started.</p>

