    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <h3 id='why_is_my_filesystem_so_small'>Why is my filesystem so small?</h3>

<p>Most images have a small partition on them by default, even though your server will have a much bigger disk. You just need to grow the partition and filesystem. See the <a href='/guides/filesystems-and-disks.html'>Filesystems and disks</a> guide</p>

<h3 id='how_do_i_resize_my_server'>How do I resize my server?</h3>

<p>We don&#8217;t support resizing in-place. You need to <a href='/guides/cli/create-a-snapshot.html'>snapshot your server</a> and create a new one using the snapshot. You&#8217;ll need to shrink the filesystem and partition if you want to resize to a smaller disk.</p>
  </div><!-- /content -->
</div><!-- /main -->


